d%20industries%20are%20already%20preparing%20for%20that%20AI%20disruption.%20In%20January%2C%20for%20example%2C%20language%20learning%20app%20Duolingo%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2024-01-08%2Fduolingo-cuts-10-of-contractors-in-move-to-greater-use-of-ai%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaxed%2010%25%20of%20its%20contract%20roles%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20saying%20that%20generative%20AI%20will%20be%20used%20to%20create%20more%20content%20moving%20forward.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22da8c08bd-aae5-49ba-8c20-f3a488d36e73%5C%22%3EWhy%20these%20jobs%20aren't%20going%20to%20disappear%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20unlikely%20that%20ChatGPT's%20new%20personal%20touch%20will%20eliminate%20professions%20in%20teaching%2C%20translation%2C%20and%20customer%20support%2C%20said%20Leslie%20Teo%2C%20senior%20director%20of%20AI%20products%20at%20AI%20Singapore%2C%20%3Cspan%3Ethe%20country's%20national%20AI%20program.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20precisely%20because%20these%20jobs%20need%20a%20personal%20touch%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20something%20about%20human%20empathy%2C%26quot%3B%20Teo%20said%2C%20highlighting%20that%20teachers%20have%20gone%20through%20the%20learning%20process%20themselves%20and%20understand%20how%20humans%20struggle%2C%20unlike%20AI.%20%26quot%3BThose%20are%20very%20powerful%20things.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETeo%20said%20that%20people%20working%20in%20teaching%2C%20translation%2C%20or%20customer%20support%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20use%20AI%20to%20make%20their%20roles%20easier%2C%20rather%20than%20be%20supplanted%20by%20technology.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20good%20customer%20service%20agent%20exudes%20empathy%20and%20understanding%2C%20something%20that%20a%20machine%20cannot%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBen%20Leong%2C%20a%20computer%20science%20professor%20at%20the%20National%20University%20of%20Singapore%2C%20said%20it's%20too%20early%20to%20draw%20conclusions%20from%20just%20a%20demo.%20He%20said%20he%20foresees%20interpreters'%20businesses%20being%20majorly%20disrupted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAI%20is%20really%20good%20for%20well-defined%20problems.%20Translation%20is%20a%20very%20well-defined%20problem%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20it's%20going%20to%20be%20much%20more%20difficult%20for%20ChatGPT%20to%20take%20over%20customer%20support%2C%20teaching%2C%20or%20negotiation%2C%20Leong%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20someone%20negotiates%20a%20bad%20deal%20for%20you%2C%20who%20is%20responsible%3F%20Are%20you%20liable%3F%20Can%20AI%20be%20your%20legal%20representative%3F%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimon%20Lucey%2C%20the%20director%20of%20the%20University%20of%20Adelaide's%20Australian%20Institute%20for%20Machine%20Learning%2C%20said%20ChatGPT%20still%20makes%20errors%20when%20multiplying%20numbers%20of%20three%20digits%20or%20more%2C%20even%20in%20its%20later%20versions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20at%20the%20moment%2C%20it's%20a%20helper.%20At%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20if%20you%20want%20to%20get%20something%20meaningful%20or%20do%20something%20reliably%2C%20you%20still%20need%20to%20get%20a%20human%20to%20cast%20desire%20over%20what%20it's%20producing%2C%26quot%3B%20Lucey%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20people%20may%20lose%20their%20jobs%20in%20the%20next%20few%20years%2C%20Lucey%20said%2C%20but%20he%20added%20that%20they%20have%20reason%20to%20stay%20optimistic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%201980s%2C%20when%20Microsoft%20released%20Excel%2C%20people%20were%20petrified%20and%20said%20it%20would%20put%20all%20of%20these%20accountants%20out%20of%20a%20job.%20We've%20got%20more%20accountants%20now%20than%20in%20the%201980s%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETeo%20agreed.%20%26quot%3BMany%20roles%20will%20be%20replaced%20by%20AI%2C%20but%20that%20doesn't%20mean%20jobs.%20Our%20jobs%20are%20bundles%20of%20roles%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%