Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%2C%20a%2027-year-old%20consultant%20who%20moved%20to%20the%20UK%20from%20Atlanta%20in%202021.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20grew%20up%20in%20a%20few%20different%20places%20%E2%80%94%20mainly%20the%20Ivory%20Coast%20and%20Atlanta.%20My%20parents%20are%20diplomats%2C%20so%20we%20moved%20around%20a%20lot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20doing%20my%20bachelor's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennial-first-time-buyer-moves-into-a-micro-home-community-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ein%20Atlanta%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20then%20I%20moved%20to%20England%20to%20do%20my%20master's.%20I%20started%20out%20in%20Southampton.%20Then%2C%20in%202022%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennial-moved-to-london-stressful-lonely-now-moving-to-portugal-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EI%20moved%20to%20London%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20always%20tell%20people%20to%20move%20to%20a%20different%20country%20in%20their%2020s%20%E2%80%94%20but%20don't%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoving-to-new-york-city-london-suprises-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emove%20to%20London%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224157a989-4db5-4b94-8948-c345512de3fb%5C%22%3EMoving%20to%20London%20can%20be%20tough%20if%20you're%20used%20to%20American%20salaries%20and%20social%20life%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20looked%20into%20moving%20to%20New%20York.%20When%20I%20saw%20the%20rents%2C%20I%20was%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BOh%2C%20this%20is%20not%20feasible.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20live%20with%20a%20roommate%2C%20pretty%20close%20to%20central%20London.%20I%20pay%20about%20%C2%A31%2C500%20(around%20%241%2C880)%20in%20rent.%20We%20have%20a%20few%20amenities%2C%20like%20a%20gym%20and%20a%20yoga%20room.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20affordable%2C%20but%20I%20think%20what%20makes%20it%20unaffordable%20is%20the%20salaries.%20For%20my%20first%20role%20after%20my%20master's%2C%20I%20was%20making%20%3Cem%3E%C2%A3%3C%2Fem%3E25%2C000%20(around%20%2426%2C900).%20My%20friend%20who%20moved%20to%20New%20York%20when%20I%20moved%20to%20London%20started%20at%20%2480%2C000.%20We%20had%20the%20same%20degree.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Atlanta%2C%20I%20was%20making%20more%20working%20part-time%20than%20I%20was%20full%20time%20in%20London.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Gladys%20Nkengasong%20wears%20all%20black%20and%20holds%20an%20umbrella%20in%20front%20of%20a%20black%20British%20taxicab.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F663e38459686a6f37bfe5d93%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221707%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENkengasong%20said%20she%20has%20had%20to%20initiate%20a%20lot%20of%20social%20interactions%20because%20people%20in%20London%20are%20less%20open%20to%20making%20new%20friends.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Gladys%20Nkengasong%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20in%20London%20tend%20to%20stick%20with%20friends%20they%20formed%20in%20school.%20My%20therapist%20was%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BIn%20London%2C%20you%20will%20be%20the%20person%20who%20has%20to%20initiate%20a%20lot.%26quot%3B%20That's%20what%20I%20found%20myself%20doing%2C%20but%20it%20gets%20so%20tiring.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20can%20get%20really%20lonely.%20You%20can%20go%20out%20and%20spend%20the%20whole%20day%20and%20not%20speak%20to%20anyone.%20Whereas%2C%20in%20Atlanta%2C%20at%20the%20gas%20station%2C%20someone's%20talking%20to%20you.%20You're%20at%20Target%2C%20someone's%20talking%20to%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESomething%20that%20affected%20my%20entire%20London%20experience%20so%20far%20is%20that%20I%20run%20into%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20who%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20negative%20sentiments%20about%20Americans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20I%20meet%20someone%20and%20they're%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BOh%2C%20where%20are%20you%20from%3F%26quot%3B%20I'm%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BCanada.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20people%20love%20Americans%2C%20and%20then%20some%20really%20don't.%20But%20I%20didn't%20realize%20how%20many%20people%20didn't%20until%20I%20moved.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d7f3f06f-6286-429e-9ea1-78208a0531cb%5C%22%3EI%20felt%20alienated%20by%20British%20drinking%20culture%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20my%20first%20job%20in%20London%2C%20people%20in%20the%20office%20would%20always%20have%20pub%20drinks%20after%20work.%20I%20used%20to%20decline%20a%20lot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20then%20my%20manager%20called%20me%20into%20a%20meeting%20and%20was%20like%2C%20'We%20just%20don't%20feel%20you're%20very%20enthusiastic.%20It%20just%20doesn't%20feel%20like%20you%20like%20being%20around%20us.%26quot%3B%20I%20had%20a%20strong%20feeling%20it%20was%20because%20of%20this%20pub%20drink%20thing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20don't%20drink%20casually.%20If%20I%20drink%2C%20we're%20celebrating%20something.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESocially%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20people's%20first%20instinct%20is%20to%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BHey%2C%20let's%20grab%20a%20drink.%20Let's%20go%20out%20to%20this%20bar%2C%20let's%20go%20to%20this%20event%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20everyone%20is%20drinking.%20It's%20just%20not%20my%20cup%20of%20tea.%20I%20started%20noticing%20that%20it%20really%20alienates%20you%20in%20London.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20going%20to%20the%20pub%2C%20and%20a%20month%20later%2C%20my%20manager%20was%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20feel%20like%20you're%20part%20of%20the%20family%20now.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20work%20at%20my%20agency%20in%20Atlanta%2C%20things%20weren't%20really%20centered%20around%20drinking.%20If%20we%20wanted%20to%20do%20something%20after%20work%2C%20it%20would%20be%2C%20like%2C%20biking.%20Or%20we%20had%20a%20communal%20area%20in%20our%20office%20and%20everyone%20would%20go%20have%20finger%20foods%2C%20chat%2C%20or%20play%20a%20game.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2233a3918f-3fce-4caa-9e03-1e5e84d2d967%5C%22%3EThere%20is%20so%20much%20about%20London%20I%20love%20%E2%80%94%20even%20the%20gray%20weather%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20US%2C%20when%20I%20go%20into%20a%20room%20or%20a%20venue%2C%20I'm%20always%20hyperaware%20of%20all%20the%20exits%20and%20where%20to%20go%20if%20something%20goes%20wrong.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20been%20at%20a%20house%20party%20that%20got%20shot%20up%2C%20and%20there%20was%20only%20one%20exit%2C%20which%20was%20the%20front%20door.%20Everyone%20was%20going%20the%20same%20way%3B%20I%20got%20trampled%20and%20sprained%20my%20ankle.%20After%20that%2C%20I%20never%20went%20to%20concerts.%20I%20thought%20it%20was%20just%20because%20I%20wasn't%20really%20a%20fan%20of%20crowds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20got%20to%20London%2C%20I%20became%20a%20concert%20person%20because%20I%20didn't%20have%20that%20paranoia%20%E2%80%94%20that%20fear%20%E2%80%94%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fshootings-stand-your-ground-us-gun-culture-experts-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egun%20violence%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Nkengasong%20in%20a%20blue-gray%20sweater%20holding%20a%20coffee%20cup%20and%20her%20cell%20phone%20in%20front%20of%20a%20building%20and%20hedges%20in%20London.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F663e372c9686a6f37bfe5c0a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221698%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENkengasong%20pivoted%20to%20consulting%20from%20working%20in%20advertising%20because%20the%20salaries%20in%20London%20were%20low.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Gladys%20Nkengasong%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI%20also%20really%20like%20the%20weather%20%E2%80%94%20I%20love%20when%20it%20gets%20cold%20and%20I%20need%20a%20jacket.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20my%20favorite%20things%20about%20London%20is%20anytime%20people%20from%20home%20come%20over%2C%20I'm%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BLet's%20take%20a%20trip.%26quot%3B%20I%20love%20that