Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fvideo%2Fnews%2Felection-junction%2Funemployment-main-problem-aspiring-doctors-to-ndtv-777107%5C%22%3Einfluence%20voter%20sentiment%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Studies%20have%20shown%20that%20employment%20rates%20and%20job%20creation%20are%20pivotal%20issues%20that%20can%20sway%20electoral%20outcomes.%20For%20instance%2C%20one%20National%20Bureau%20of%20Economic%20Research%20working%20paper%20highlighted%20that%20changes%20in%20employment%20and%20wages%20significantly%20impact%20voter%20turnout%20and%20preferences%20in%20gubernatorial%20elections%2C%20suggesting%20that%20economic%20performance%20is%20a%20critical%20factor%20in%20political%20campaigns.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5CnMoreover%2C%20political%20discourse%20often%20leverages%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fyoung-indians-more-likely-to-be-unemployed-if-theyre-educated-says-report-5332275%5C%22%3Eemployment%20statistics%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20frame%20narratives%20or%20critique%20opposing%20parties%2C%20as%20seen%20in%20India's%20recent%20elections%2C%20where%20opposition%20leaders%20used%20reports%20such%20as%20the%20International%20Labour%20Organization's%20(ILO)%20India%20Employment%20Report%202024%20to%20raise%20the%20issue%20of%20unemployment.%20The%20report%20revealed%20that%20since%202019%2C%20the%20majority%20of%20new%20work%20has%20been%20through%20self-employment%2C%20predominantly%20among%20unpaid%20family%20workers%2C%20who%20are%20mainly%20women.%20The%20report%20highlights%20an%20increase%20in%20employment%20within%20the%20agricultural%20sector%20and%20notes%20a%20concerning%20stagnation%20in%20the%20manufacturing%20sector's%20employment%20share.%20%C2%A0The%20report%20further%20revealed%20that%20unemployment%20rose%20from%205.7%25%20in%202000%20to%2017.5%25%20in%202019%2C%20decreasing%20to%2012.4%25%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EMethodological%20Issues%20With%20The%20Report%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20goes%20without%20saying%20that%20one%20of%20the%20primary%20responsibilities%20of%20any%20government%20is%20to%20establish%20a%20favourable%20environment%20that%20encourages%20the%20creation%20of%20job%20opportunities.%20However%2C%20there%20are%20some%20methodological%20issues%20with%20the%20report.%20This%20has%20been%20already%20highlighted%20by%20the%20Chief%20Economic%20Advisor%2C%20V%20Anantha%20Nageswaram%2C%20and%20TCA%20Anant.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5CnThe%20report%20utilises%20data%20from%20various%20sources%2C%20such%20as%20the%20National%20Sample%20Survey%20(NSS)%20from%201999-00%20and%202011-12%20and%20the%20Periodic%20Labour%20Force%20Survey%20(PLFS)%20from%202018-19%20and%202021-22%2C%20leading%20to%20potential%20discontinuities%20in%20the%20data%20timeline.%20This%20gap%20between%20datasets%20obscures%20significant%20labour%20market%20trends%20and%20transitions%2C%20particularly%20around%20key%20economic%20reforms%20and%20policy%20changes%20that%20occurred%20in%20the%20interim%20years%2C%20such%20as%20the%20economic%20shifts%20following%20demonetisation.%20The%20lack%20of%20continuous%20data%20makes%20it%20difficult%20to%20assess%20whether%20observed%20employment%20trends%20are%20consistent%20over%20time%20or%20whether%20they%20are%20simply%20the%20result%20of%20specific%20policy%20impacts%20or%20global%20economic%20conditions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fyoung-indians-more-likely-to-be-unemployed-if-theyre-educated-says-report-5332275%5C%22%3ERead%20%7C%C2%A0Young%20Indians%20More%20Likely%20To%20Be%20Unemployed%20If%20They're%20Educated%2C%20Says%20Report%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5CnFurthermore%2C%20the%20shift%20from%20NSS%20to%20PLFS%20introduces%20complexity%20due%20to%20differences%20in%20methodology%2C%20frequency%2C%20and%20possibly%20coverage%20and%20sampling%20techniques.%20While%20the%20NSS%20provides%20quinquennial%20snapshots%20of%20employment%2C%20the%20annual%20PLFS%20aims%20for%20more%20frequent%20updates%20but%20may%20differ%20in%20how%20it%20categorises%20employment%20or%20the%20working-age%20population.%20Direct%20comparisons%20without%20adjusting%20for%20these%20methodological%20differences%20could%20lead%20to%20misleading%20conclusions%20about%20employment%20trends.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EUnemployment%20Varies%20Across%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGoing%20beyond%20this%20report%2C%20one%20should%20also%20look%20at%20the%20spatial%20distribution%20of%20unemployment%20in%20India.%20PLFS%202022-23%20data%20shows%20that%20the%20unemployment%20in%20India%20is%203.17%25.%20However%2C%20there%20are%20states%20that%20are%20way%20above%20the%20national%20average%3A%20Goa%20(9.7%25)%2C%20Kerala%20(7%25)%2C%20Haryana%20(6.1%25)%2C%20Punjab%20(6.1%25)%20and%20Meghalaya%20(6.0%25).%20The%20unemployment%20rate%20is%20lowest%20in%20Assam%20(1.7%25).%20Tripura%2C%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20Jharkhand%2C%20Assam%20%26amp%3B%20Gujarat%20have%20the%20lowest%20unemployment%20rate%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20fact%20misrepresented%20by%20the%20media%20is%20that%20the%20ILO%20report%20has%20suggested%20that%2082.9%25%20of%20youth%20are%20unemployed.%20However%2C%20to%20be%20fair%20to%20the%20ILO%20report%2C%20it%20has%20said%20that%20the%20share%20of%20unemployed%20youth%20in%20the%20total%20unemployed%20population%20was%2082.9%25.%20Irrespective%20of%20that%2C%20PLFS%202022-23%2C%20the%20unemployment%20rate%20in%20India%20for%20individuals%20aged%2015%20and%20older%2C%20based%20on%20their%20highest%20education%20level%2C%20varies%20significantly.%20The%20rate%20for%20those%20who%20finished%20middle%20school%20is%201.7%25%2C%20while%20it%20increases%20to%202.2%25%20for%20secondary%20school%20completers.%20Higher%20secondary%20completers%20face%20an%20unemployment%20rate%20of%204.6%25.%20The%20rates%20escalate%20for%20those%20with%20higher%20qualifications%3A%2012.2%25%20for%20diploma%20holders%2C%2013.4%25%20for%20graduates%2C%20and%2012.1%25%20for%20postgraduates%20and%20above.%20Those%20with%20at%20least%20a%20secondary%20school%20education%20experience%20a%207.3%25%20unemployment%20rate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EUnemployment%20And%20Education%3A%20A%20Paradox%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20points%20to%20the%20fact%20that%20unemployment%2C%20sometimes%2C%20can%20paradoxically%20increase%20with%20the%20level%20of%20education%20primarily%20due%20to%20three%20factors.%20First%2C%20highly%20educated%20individuals%20often%20have%20specific%20career%20expectations%20and%20may%20not%20settle%20for%20jobs%20that%20they%20perceive%20as%20underutilising%20their%20skills%2C%20leading%20to%20longer%20periods%20of%20job-seeking.%20In%20FY24%2C%20despite%20the%20significant%20growth%20in%20job%20vacancies%20on%20the%20National%20Career%20Service%20(NCS)%20portal%2C%20which%20soared%20by%20214%25%20to%2010%2C924%2C161%20positions%20compared%20to%203%2C481%2C944%20the%20previous%20year%2C%20there%20was%20only%20a%2053%25%20increase%20in%20job-seeker%20registrations%2C%20totalling%2087%2C27%2C900.%20This%20discrepancy%20highlights%20a%20surprising%20trend%20of%20fewer%20job-seekers%20relative%20to%20the%20burgeoning%20job%20opportunities%2C%20reflecting%20a%20mismatch%20in%20job%20requirements%20or%20awareness.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fif-selling-pakodas-is-a-job-begging-a-job-too-p-chidambaram-s-swipe-at-pm-narendra-modi-1805593%5C%22%3ERead%20%7C%20If%20Selling%C2%A0%3Ci%3EPakodas%3C%2Fi%3E%C2%A0Is%20A%20Job%2C%20Begging%20A%20Job%20Too%3A%20P%20Chidambaram's%20Swipe%20At%20PM%20Modi%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESecond%2C%20the%20job%20market%20may%20need%20more%20high-skill%20positions%20available%20to%20match%20the%20growing%20number%20of%20graduates%2C%20creating%20an%20imbalance%20between%20supply%20and%20demand.%20This%20situation%20is%20exacerbated%20by%20rapid%20changes%20in%20technology%20and%20global%20economic%20structures%2C%20which%20can%20make%20certain%20specialised%20skills%20obsolete%20more%20quickly.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5CnThird%2C%20higher%20education%20can%20sometimes%20be%20misaligned%20with%20the%20labour%20market's%20actual%20needs%2C%20leading%20to%20a%20mismatch%20where%20the%20workforce's%20qualifications%20do%20not%20meet%20the%20requirements%20of%20available%20jobs.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5CnTo%20specifically%20address%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffeature%2Finternet-debates-after-harsh-goenka-highlights-shortage-of-skilled-workers-in-india-4321337%5C%22%3EIndia's%20skill%20gap%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20revealed%20by%20the%20India%20Skills%20Report%202024%2C%20several%20targeted%20strategies%20can%20be%20implemented.%20For%20regions%20like%20Andhra%20Pradesh%2C%20West%20Bengal%2C%20and%20Delhi%2C%20which%20show%20higher%20employability%20rates%2C%20tailored%20initiatives%20to%20boost%20local%20skills%20can%20be%20replicated%20in%20regions%20with%20lower%20employability.%20Emphasising%20emerging%20technologies%20in%20educational%20curricula%2C%20such%20as%20in%20Electronics%20and%20Communication%20Engineering%20(ECE)%20and%20Information%20Technology%20(IT)%2C%20can%20help%20meet%20the%20high%20demand%20for%20skills%20in%20these%20areas.%20Moreover%2C%20expanding%20public-private%20partnerships%20can%20ensure%20that%20educational%20programmes%20align%20closely%20with%20industry%20needs%2C%20particularly%20in%20fast-growing%20fields%20highlighted%20by%20the%20impact%20of%20AI%20on%20future%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20India%20Needs%20To%20Focus%20On%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurthermore%2C%20vocational%20training%20needs%20strengthening%20to%20provide%20practical%20skills%20quickly%20and%20effectively%2C%20addressing%20immediate%20skill%20demands%20in%20various%20trades%20and%20technical%20roles.%20Policy%20incentives%20for%20lifelong%20learning%2C%20including%20tax%20breaks%20and%20subsidised%20training%20programs%2C%20can%20motivate%20ongoing%20skill%20development%20among%20the%20workforce.%20To%20ensure%20these%20measures%20are%20effective%2C%20a%20robust%20monitoring%20framework%20should%20be%20established%20to%20evaluate%20the%20impact%20of%20these%20policies%20and%20adapt%20them%20as%20needed%2C%20ensuring%20they%20meet%20the%20evolving%20demands%20of%20India's%20labour%20market%20and%20effectively%20reduce%20the%20skill%20gap.%20The%20new%20government%20should%20make%20this%20a%20priority%20in%20the%20next%20term.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5CnWith%20that%20said%2C%20India%20needs%20to%20create%20more%20jobs.%20India's%20population%20growth%20rate%20has%20decreased%20to%20about%200.8%25%20from%20the%20earlier%20figures%20of%201.3%25%20or%201.5%25.%20Concurrently%2C%20the%20number%20of%20children%20in%20the%200%20to%2015%20age%20brackets%20has%20not%20only%20proportionately%20declined%20but%20also%20in%20absolute%20numbers%20since%202019.%20Past%20job%20creation%20targets%20suggested%20by%20entities%20like%20the%20SP%20Gupta%20Committee%20or%20the%20Montek%20Singh%20Ahluwalia%20committee%20of%20the%20former%20planning%20commission%20-%20around%2010%20to%2012%20million%20jobs%20annually%20-%20are%20now%20outdated%3B%20a%20more%20realistic%20figure%20might%20be%20closer%20to%208%20million%20jobs%20per%20year%20considering%20the%20current%20economic%20growth%20rate.%20However%2C%20the%20reality%20seems%20to%20be%20that%20we're%20creating%20less%20than%20this%20number%20annually.%20The%20declining%20employment%20elasticity%20of%20growth%20has%20been%20going%20on%20for%20more%20than%20two%20decades.%20It's%20not%20a%20new%20phenomenon.%20This%20should%20change.%20The%20enabling%20reforms%20over%20the%20last%20decade%20will%20help%20the%20next%20government%20achieve%20this%20target.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cem%3E(Bibek%20Debroy%20is%20Chairman%2C%20Economic%20Advisory%20Council%20to%20the%20Prime%20Minister.%20Aditya%20Sinha%20is%20Officer%20on%20Special%20Duty%2C%20Research%2C%20Economic%20Advisory%20Council%20to%20the%20Prime%20Minister)%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1715675280000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-03%2Fg5et1fg_unemployment_625x300_01_March_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Findias-employment-challenge-needs-informed-solutions-not-hasty-conclusions-5660251%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22India%20needs%20to%20create%20more%20jobs.%20A%20realistic%20figure%20might%20be%20closer%20to%208%20million%20jobs%20per%20year%20considering%20the%20current%20economic%20growth%20rate.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Findias-employment-challenge-needs-informed-solutions-not-hasty-conclusions-5660251%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22FPIs%20sell%20shares%20worth%20over%20Rs%2022%2C000%20crore%20in%20May%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1715675254000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-110111189%2Cimgsize-111300.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fbusiness%2Findia-business%2Fforeign-portfolio-investors-sell-shares-worth-over-rs-22000-crore-in-may-what-should-your-strategy-be%2Farticleshow%2F110110319.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Foreign%20portfolio%20investors%20(FPIs)%20selling%20Indian%20stocks%20worth%20Rs%2022%2C000%20crore%20in%20May%20have%20led%20to%20a%20significant%20impact%20on%20companies%20with%20high%20foreign%20ownership.%20Over%20100%20stocks%2C%20with%20FPI%20stakes%20of%20more%20than%205%25%2C%20have%20seen%20declines%20of%2010%25%20to%2030%25%20in%20the%20last%20month.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20BUSINESS%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2