22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-explains-news-gen-zers-improve-media-literacy-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emedia%20literacy%3C%2Fa%3E%20they%20need%20to%20process%20the%20images%20around%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20conversations%20aren't%20always%20easy.%20That's%20why%20I%20created%20the%20nonprofit%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthepconversation.org%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Porn%20Conversation%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20give%20families%20tools%20to%20help%20them%20talk%20with%20kids%20about%20porn%20literacy.%20Parents%20play%20a%20huge%20role%20in%20helping%20teens%20make%20decisions%20around%20sex%20%E2%80%94%20and%20if%20you%20can%20get%20on%20a%20level%20with%20your%20kids%20where%20you%20can%20have%20open%20conversations%20and%20they%20know%20they%20can%20trust%20you%2C%20you%20have%20gained%20a%20lot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20how%20I've%20talked%20to%20my%20kids%20about%20porn.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c3cfaad8-cc18-4990-ab09-ea5fbdca6429%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20started%20by%20teaching%20them%20the%20correct%20names%20for%20their%20body%20parts%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20key%20to%20creating%20an%20open%20dialogue%20with%20your%20kids%20about%20porn%20is%20having%20conversations%20about%20sexuality.%20That%20starts%20with%20teaching%20children%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fparents-should-teach-kids-call-genitals-penis-vagina-sex-education-2021-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecorrect%20words%20for%20their%20body%20parts%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20taught%20my%20children%20words%20like%20vulva%2C%20vagina%2C%20penis%2C%20and%20clitoris%20from%20a%20young%20age.%20Giving%20them%20the%20right%20vocabulary%20helps%20them%20express%20ideas%20and%20feelings.%20Later%20on%2C%20I%20also%20helped%20them%20understand%20that%20there%20are%20parts%20of%20our%20bodies%20that%20give%20us%20pleasure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKnowing%20these%20words%20and%20what%20their%20body%20parts%20do%20helps%20kids%20protect%20their%20bodies%20and%20feel%20bodily%20autonomy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221d351e00-10bc-46e7-8a88-e07fab25eff6%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20welcome%20their%20curiosity%20without%20making%20them%20feel%20ashamed%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20kids%20get%20older%2C%20they%20may%20hear%20about%20things%20in%20the%20schoolyard%20that%20make%20parents%20nervous.%20They%20might%20suddenly%20come%20up%20to%20you%20and%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BHey%20mom%2C%20what's%20a%20blowjob%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20can%20catch%20you%20off%20guard%2C%20but%20reacting%20in%20a%20way%20that%20doesn't%20make%20them%20feel%20ashamed%20or%20judged%20is%20critical%20to%20building%20trust.%20Don't%20interrogate%20them%20by%20asking%20them%20where%20they%20heard%20that%20word%20or%20tell%20them%20they%20shouldn't%20talk%20about%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20I%20try%20to%20be%20neutral%20and%20explain%20the%20technicalities%20of%20it%20without%20focusing%20on%20the%20sexual%20notions.%20I%20also%20explain%20that%20these%20things%20belong%20to%20an%20adult%20world%20of%20play.%20Introducing%20that%20concept%20early%20can%20help%20them%20understand%20the%20purpose%20of%20porn%20later%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnytime%20we%20have%20sensitive%20conversations%2C%20I%20remind%20my%20kids%20that%20they%20can%20ask%20me%20anything%20and%20that%20I%20will%20never%20judge%20them%20for%20who%20they%20are%20or%20what%20they're%20curious%20about.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22769b2312-5eb1-48aa-a21b-b11ca12cf6a3%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20explain%20that%20porn%20is%20for%20adults%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20if%20you%20don't%20like%20the%20idea%20that%20your%20child%20might%20be%20exposed%20to%20porn%2C%20it's%20something%20we%20all%20have%20to%20face%20because%20we've%20given%20technology%20to%20our%20kids.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaybe%20you%20see%20an%20adults-only%20tab%20opened%20on%20their%20tablet's%20browser%20or%20find%20it%20in%20their%20browsing%20history.%20They%20might%20even%20tell%20you%20directly%20that%20they%20came%20across%20something%20and%20didn't%20know%20what%20to%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20(or%20when)%20this%20happens%2C%20don't%20panic.%20Take%20a%20breath%20and%20set%20the%20tone%20for%20a%20casual%20conversation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExplain%20who%20porn%20is%20for.%20I'd%20tell%20my%20child%2C%20%26quot%3BThese%20films%20are%20made%20for%20people%2018%20and%20above%2C%20and%20they're%20not%20for%20you%2C%20but%20now%20that%20you've%20seen%20it%2C%20I'd%20like%20to%20talk%20to%20you%20about%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228e2bc515-44e5-4f3e-abfe-4ba4c6856f82%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20share%20my%20perspective%20on%20porn%20and%20keep%20the%20conversation%20two-sided%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20also%20share%20my%20perspective%20on%20what%20they%20might%20have%20seen.%20Most%20free%20online%20porn%20perpetuates%20harmful%20stereotypes%2C%20often%20objectifying%20women%20and%20portraying%20sexual%20violence.%20I%20point%20out%20these%20issues%20and%20let%20them%20know%20that%2C%20just%20like%20in%20an%20action%20movie%2C%20this%20isn't%20how%20things%20are%20in%20real%20life.%20And%20seeing%20these%20images%20online%20can%20be%20harmful.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20time%20they%20see%20porn%2C%20these%20ideas%20will%20start%20spinning.%20Maybe%20they%20even%20think%2C%20%26quot%3BThat%20thing%20my%20mom%20said%20is%20true%2C%20and%20I%20don't%20like%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20conversation%20has%20to%20be%20two-sided%2C%20though.%20I%20recommend%20asking%20your%20child%20about%20how%20what%20they%20saw%20made%20them%20feel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20kids%20might%20not%20want%20to%20talk%20about%20it%2C%20although%20some%20will.%20But%20the%20most%20important%20thing%20is%20for%20them%20to%20understand%20that%20if%20they%20want%20to%20talk%20about%20it%2C%20you're%20willing%20to%20have%20a%20conversation.%20They%20need%20to%20know%20that%20you%20are%20there%20for%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fb11730c-bc92-4077-98ff-b842fefad8a1%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20find%20teachable%20moments%20to%20build%20media%20literacy%20skills%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20I%20worry%20most%20about%20as%20a%20parent%20and%20human%20being%20is%20not%20that%20a%20child%20has%20seen%20porn%20but%20that%20they%20might%20not%20know%20how%20to%20process%20these%20images.%20They%20need%20media%20literacy%20skills%20to%20understand%20that%20pornography%20is%20fiction%2C%20that%20it's%20created%20by%20professionals%20to%20look%20a%20certain%20way%2C%20and%20that%20much%20of%20it%20contains%20coded%20messages%20about%20sexism%20and%20racism.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20can't%20say%20all%20porn%20is%20bad%20%E2%80%94%20there%20are%20a%20bunch%20of%20creators%20who%20are%20fighting%20for%20a%20different%20kind%20of%20pornography%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20inclusivity%2C%20diversity%2C%20sexuality%2C%20gender%20roles%2C%20and%20erotic%20imagery.%20In%20many%20senses%2C%20it's%20better%20than%20it%20has%20ever%20been%20before.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20throughout%20my%20children's%20lives%2C%20I've%20looked%20for%20teachable%20moments%20to%20help%20them%20build%20literacy%20skills%2C%20which%20ultimately%20feed%20into%20larger%20conversations%20about%20porn%20as%20they've%20gotten%20older.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20can%20use%20a%20Disney%20film%20to%20spark%20conversations%20about%20gender%20roles%20by%20asking%2C%20%26quot%3BWhy%20do%20you%20think%20the%20princess%20is%20shown%20that%20way%3F%26quot%3B%20Or%20if%20you%20see%20your%20kid%20following%20an%20influencer%20who%20is%20promoting%20products%2C%20you%20can%20ask%20them%20if%20they%20think%20they%20%3Cem%3Ereally%3C%2Fem%3E%20love%20those%20items%20or%20if%20they're%20doing%20it%20for%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPointing%20out%20the%20things%20we%20see%20and%20questioning%20them%20helps%20children%20build%20the%20skills%20they'll%20need%20to%20understand%20porn.%3C%2