h2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECometary%20globules%2C%20first%20noticed%20in%201976%2C%20have%20no%20connection%20with%20comets.%20These%20are%20dense%2C%20compact%20clouds%20of%20gas%20and%20dust%20in%20space%20shaped%20like%20comets%20with%20a%20long%2C%20faintly%20glowing%20tail.%20They%20typically%20contain%20newborn%20stars%20in%20their%20cores%20and%20are%20created%20by%20the%20heavy%20radiation%20from%20nearby%20stars.%20Cometary%20globules%20play%20a%C2%A0major%C2%A0role%20in%C2%A0the%20process%20of%C2%A0stellar%20birth%20and%20evolution%20within%20galaxies.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cb%3EWhat%20Is%20God's%C2%A0Hand%3F%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20recent%20images%20of%20%26quot%3BGod's%C2%A0Hand%26quot%3B%20show%20CG%204%2C%20a%20cometary%20globule%20found%20within%20the%20Milky%20Way%20galaxy%20in%20the%20constellation%20'Puppis'%2C%C2%A01%2C300%20light%20years%20away.%20CG%204%20has%20a%20main%20dusty%20head%2C%20resembling%20a%20twisting%20hand%2C%20measuring%201.5%20light-years%20across%2C%20with%20a%20lengthy%20tail%20extending%C2%A08%C2%A0light%20years.%20(A%20light%20year%20is%20the%20distance%20light%20travels%20in%20one%20year%2C%20equivalent%20to%20approximately%209.46%20trillion%20kilometres).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGod's%C2%A0Hand%26quot%3B%20appears%20to%20be%20reaching%20toward%20a%20distant%20spiral%20galaxy%20named%20ESO%20257-19%20(PGC%2021338)%2C%20over%20100%20million%20light%20years%20away.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20named%20%26quot%3BGod's%20Hand%26quot%3B%2C%20there%20is%20nothing%20supernatural%20about%20the%20celestial%20structure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20captivating%20picture%20of%20CG%204%C2%A0is%20taken%C2%A0by%20the%20DECam%20(Dark%20Energy%20Camera)%2C%20a%20high-tech%20tool%20on%20the%20Victor%20M%20Blanco%20Telescope%20in%C2%A0Chile%C2%A0situated%20at%207%2C200%20feet%20above%20sea%20level.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAstronomers%C2%A0stumbled%20upon%20cometary%20globules%20by%20accident%C2%A0in%201976%20while%20stud