0Picture%20source%3A%20Facebook%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2FNagpurBookClub%2Fposts%2Fmaharaja-sayajirao-gaekwad-iii-opened-the-first-mobile-library-in-the-state-of-b%2F131188458227933%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENagpur%20Book%20Club%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20travelling%20libraries%20are%20common%2C%20and%20a%20loved%20concept.%20But%20over%20130%20years%20ago%2C%20they%20were%20nothing%20short%20of%20a%20marvel%2C%20a%20miracle%20if%20you%20will.%20It%20wouldn%E2%80%99t%20be%20a%20stretch%20to%20say%20that%20it%20was%20Maharaja%20Sayajirao%20Gaekwad%20III%20who%20started%20first-of-its-kind%20mobile%20libraries%20when%20he%20introduced%20the%20concept%20in%20the%20erstwhile%20Baroda%20state%20to%20encourage%20reading.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20went%20on%20to%20reform%20the%20state%20with%20his%20initiatives.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F348905%2Fhydroponics-training-workshop-in-gujarat-india-rasik-nakum-one-farm-hydroponics-rajkot-teaching-soil-less-water-less-farming%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAn%20interesting%20story%20%3C%2Fa%3Eoften%20told%20is%20how%20the%20Maharaja%20was%20a%20humble%20boy%20who%20ascended%20the%20throne%20because%20of%20his%20quick%20wit.%20In%201870%2C%20Maharaja%20Khanderao%20Gaekwad%20II%20passed%20away%2C%20leaving%20behind%20his%20widow%20who%20decided%20to%20start%20looking%20for%20an%20heir.%20She%20called%20the%20heads%20of%20the%20extended%20family%20of%20Gaekwad%20to%20Baroda%20deciding%20to%20screen%20the%20youngsters%20with%20a%20test.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20Shrimant%20Kashirao%20Gaekwad%20presented%20himself%20before%20the%20queen%20with%20his%20three%20sons%2C%20she%20asked%20them%20the%20purpose%20of%20their%20arrival.%20It%20was%20Gopalrao%E2%80%99s%20answer%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20have%20come%20her